\title{Addition of linear maps}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-09}
\taxon{definition}
\meta{source}{[[axler-1996-linear]] Definition 3.5}
\meta{source}{[[lankham-2016-linear]] Section 6.1}

\p{Let #{V} and #{W} be vector spaces over #{\FF}. Let #{S,T\in\mathcal{L}(V,W)} be linear transformations from #{V} to #{W}. Then we may define the \define{Sum} of #{S} and #{T} to be the linear transformation #{S+T} defined by #{(S+T)(v)=S(v)+T(v)} for all #{v\in V}.}